HEADWORD: Epencephalon
<hw>Ep`en*ceph"a*lon</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <grk>'epi`</grk> upon, near + <?/ brain.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>The segment of the brain next behind the midbrain, including the
cerebellum and pons; the hindbrain. Sometimes abbreviated to
<abbr>epen.</abbr></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

